---
import Buffer from '../layouts/Buffer.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../../site.config';
---

<Buffer
  title={`about.md — ${siteConfig.name}`}
  description="Longer bio: the arc, the research, what pulls him toward storage and data systems."
  currentPath="/about"
>
  <!-- TODO(owner): this page is a drafted starting point, not final copy —
       review voice/tone and every claim below before ship (SPEC.md §12.2). -->
  <div class="line">
    <h1>about.md</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="line">
    <p>
      My path has run through the University of Washington, where I'm finishing a BS in Computer
      Science ({siteConfig.education.split(', ').pop()}), through undergraduate research on
      AI–human coding collaboration, and into a role as a {siteConfig.role}. TODO(owner): one
      sentence on what the day job actually involves day to day — kept brief, no internal
      specifics (SPEC.md §13).
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="line">
    <p>
      What pulls me toward storage and data systems is the layer underneath everything else:
      {siteConfig.focus}. TODO(owner): a real sentence or two on what draws you here specifically
      — a project, a bug, a book, a professor — rather than the generic version above.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="line">
    <p>TODO(owner): a paragraph on where you're headed next — the throughline from now.md's building/learning arc to what you want to be doing in a year or two.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="line">
    <h2>research</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="line">
    <p>
      At UW I researched AI–human coding collaboration and built{' '}
      {siteConfig.links.hedwig ? (
        <a href={siteConfig.links.hedwig} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hedwig</a>
      ) : (
        <span>Hedwig <span class="pending-note">(landing page link pending)</span></span>
      )}, an adaptive governance layer for LLM coding agents — learning when an agent should act
      autonomously versus defer to the developer. TODO(owner): the award, in one clause, with
      exact wording (SPEC.md §14 item 4). Full detail lives at the landing page and{' '}
      {siteConfig.links.paper ? (
        <a href={siteConfig.links.paper} target="_blank" rel="noopener">the paper</a>
      ) : (
        <span class="pending-note">the paper (link pending)</span>
      )}, not re-argued here.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="line">
    <p class="pending-note">
      TODO(owner): optional closing paragraph of non-work texture — your call on what's public
      (SPEC.md §14 item 7). Omitted for now.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="line">
    <p class="contact-line">
      {
        siteConfig.links.github ? (
          <a href={siteConfig.links.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener">gh</a>
        ) : (
          <span class="pending-note">gh (pending)</span>
        )
      }
      <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span>
      {
        siteConfig.links.linkedin ? (
          <a href={siteConfig.links.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener">in</a>
        ) : (
          <span class="pending-note">in (pending)</span>
        )
      }
      <span aria-hidden="true"> · </span>
      {
        siteConfig.email ? (
          <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>@</a>
        ) : (
          <span class="pending-note">@ (pending)</span>
        )
      }
    </p>
  </div>
</Buffer>

<style>
  .pending-note {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }

  .contact-line a {
    color: var(--foam);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
